 U.S. soldiers arrived Thursday in Russia's southern Urals to take part in a 
joint peacekeeping exercise. The 250 servicemen will be the first U.S. soldiers 
to hold maneuvers on Russian soil. 
</P>
<P>
 The joint maneuvers, scheduled to run from today to Sept 10, are designed to 
