WALTER RAINES; DIRECTOR OF HARLEM DANCE THEATER SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Walter Raines, 54, artistic director of the School for Dance Theater of 
Harlem.A native of Pennsylvania, Raines studied dance at Pittsburgh Playhouse 
School of Theatre & Dance, Carnegie-Mellon University and the School of 
American Ballet. He danced with the Pennsylvania and Stuttgart ballets, and 
became a charter member of the Harlem troupe in 1969. He later switched to 
teaching at City University of New York, and served as chairman of the ballet 
department of the Alvin Ailey American Dance Center. Raines became co-director 
of the Harlem school in 1989 and sole director a year later. On Sunday in New 
York of AIDS. 
</P>
