<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUS PASSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I was very disappointed to learn that the major reason the MTA is 
discontinuing its monthly bus passes is due to the number of counterfeit ones 
that have been circulating. 
</P>
<P>
 Woe to the society that succumbs to its small criminal element over the vast 
majority of hard-working people who rely on public transportation to get them 
to their jobs! Rather than making public transportation easier and more 
accessible to the people in this age of traffic and air pollution, we are 
taking a giant step backward as we let the lawbreakers have the last word. 
</P>
<P>
 How about having more police investigating counterfeit activity and 
incorporating stiffer sentences for those convicted?  
</P>
<P>
 PAUL MALEVITZ 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
