<HEADLINE>
<P>
SMOG PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * I applaud Mayor Richard Riordan's decision to get involved with the AQMD 
smog plan (Aug. 10). Next he should lobby the federal government to allocate a 
substantial commitment of land and water conservation funds for the L.A. 
region.These are moneys paid to the federal government by the oil companies to 
mitigate pollution caused by oil drilling. 
</P>
<P>
 It is scandalous that the federal government is hoarding funds ($800 million 
per year) created to mitigate pollution caused by oil drilling, while at the 
same time threatening us with sanctions for not meeting federal air quality 
standards.  
</P>
<P>
 Please join us in our efforts to loosen land and water conservation funds to 
preserve critical airshed, such as the 5,400-acre Ahmanson Ranch, located next 
to the smoggy San Fernando Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 ROSIE McCABE 
</P>
<P>
 Save Open Space 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Monica Mountains 
</P>
<P>
 Agoura 
</P>
</TEXT>
