<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUL OF THE MATTER SHARP IN COMEBACK VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE DISTEL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Burt Bacharach had not been to a racetrack since the Kentucky Derby. 
Coincidentally, neither had his 3-year-old, Soul Of The Matter.Bacharach was at 
Del Mar Thursday to watch his horse make his comeback run. 
</P>
<P>
 "I've got a 7:30 a.m. flight to Houston tomorrow," Bacharach said. "I hope 
this whole trip is worthwhile." 
</P>
<P>
 Soul Of The Matter, fifth in the Derby, had been kept in the stable because of 
hoof injuries until blowing away the allowance field in Thursday's eighth race. 
Jockey Kent Desormeaux had him seven lengths behind a pack of five horses 
entering the stretch. When Desormeaux finally found a hole, Soul Of The Matter 
breezed to victory. 
</P>
<P>
 "He had all kinds of excuses to lose," Bacharach said. "He was trapped, 
trapped, trapped. It seemed Kent had nowhere to take him." 
</P>
<P>
 Soul Of The Matter has four victories in eight starts, finishing out of the 
money only in the Kentucky Derby. Trainer Richard Mandella said he has no 
schedule set for his next start. DAVE DISTEL 
</P>
</TEXT>
