<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; READING CLUB FOR CHILDREN PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A reading club for preschool children will begin at the Fullerton Library on 
Sept. 13. 
</P>
<P>
 The free "Hungry Caterpillar Club" will meet Tuesdays at 11:15 a.m. at Hunt 
Branch Library, 201 S. Basque Ave., and Wednesdays at 11:15 a.m. and Thursdays 
at 10:30 a.m. at the Main Library, 353 W. Commonwealth Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 The club's name comes from the children's book "The Very Hungry Caterpillar," 
by Eric Carle. The book celebrates its 25th anniversary this year, library 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Club members will be treated to puppet shows, songs, craft activities, films 
and readings of picture books, poems, nursery rhymes and folklore. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration is required and children may sign up for the club at either of 
the participating libraries. For more information, call (714) 738-3121. 
</P>
</TEXT>
