<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; USC; WOODS LOOKS WEST AT TROJAN CAREER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 USC is in the hunt for one of the nation's top-rated high school quarterbacks, 
Quincy Woods of Park Forest, Ill. 
</P>
<P>
 Woods, 6 feet 2 and 185 pounds, also is being recruited by Notre Dame but has 
narrowed his possible choices to Florida State, Nebraska, North Carolina and 
USC, according to the Chicago Sun-Times. 
</P>
<P>
 Trojan quarterback Rob Johnson is a senior. The backups are sophomores Brad 
Otton and Matt Koffler. Junior Kyle Wachholtz is academically ineligible this 
year and has one season remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 One NFL player personnel director, Bob Ackles of the Arizona Cardinals, rates 
two Trojans, quarterback Johnson and offensive tackle Tony Boselli, as 
potential first-round choices in the next draft. 
</P>
<P>
 "With a good year, there's no reason why Johnson shouldn't be a first-round 
pick," Ackles said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Two other possible early quarterback picks, the way things stand now, would 
be Eric Zeier (of Georgia) and Steve McNair (of Alcorn State). 
</P>
<P>
 "Johnson's big pluses are his short-to-medium accuracy. His deep-ball accuracy 
isn't great yet, but it's good. His running ability is a negative, but a lot of 
good quarterbacks don't run well. 
</P>
<P>
 "Boselli's pluses are obvious: Outstanding size (at 6-7 1/2 and 320), very 
quick set-up on pass blocking, poise." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Freshman wide receiver Ken Haslip injured a knee in practice Wednesday and 
still is undergoing evaluation. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
