<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAYBERRY SUSPENDED AFTER HORSE FAILS TEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE DISTEL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Trainer Brian Mayberry was suspended for 30 days by the California Horse 
Racing Board Thursday because of what CHRB stewards at Del Mar said was a 
positive drug test on a horse he ran at Hollywood Park on July 6. 
</P>
<P>
 The ruling said that Gamblin A.J., trained by Mayberry at the time, was found 
with a foreign substance -- promazine sulfoxide -- in his urine after the sixth 
race that day.Steward Dave Samuel described promazine sulfoxide as a 
tranquilizer. 
</P>
<P>
 Gamblin A.J. was claimed by trainer Mike Mitchell out of that Hollywood Park 
field and is scheduled to run in Saturday's Del Mar Debutante out of the 
Mitchell barn. 
</P>
<P>
 According to the terms of the suspension, Mayberry loses his license 
privileges and is denied access to all premises within the CHRB's jurisdiction. 
The 30-day period will begin next Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Thursday's feature race was won by Soul Of The Matter, making its first start 
since finishing fifth in the Kentucky Derby. DAVE DISTEL 
</P>
</TEXT>
