<HEADLINE>
<P>
DISNEYLAND GIVES LOCALS A BREAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In another sign of dwindling attendance, Disneyland said Thursday that it will 
begin a locals-only discount admission today that will slash an entry ticket to 
$23, an $8 price break. 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California residents who can show proof of their address may buy as 
many as eight discounted tickets.The $23 ticket costs the same for adults and 
children. Regular prices are $31 for adults and $25 for children age 3 to 11. 
</P>
<P>
 Disneyland instituted similar price cuts at the start of California's 
recession, during the winter season. Until then, the park had never offered 
across-the-board discounts. 
</P>
<P>
 Attendance has dropped at both Walt Disney Co.'s original theme park in 
Anaheim and Walt Disney World in Florida. As a result, company officials have 
warned of impending staff cuts and have threatened to contract out such 
services as staffing the employee cafeteria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
