<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONSUMER AFFAIRS / DENISE GELLENE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENISE GELLENE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Odds and ends: The National Cattlemen's Assn. says Americans will eat 52 
million pounds of beef on Labor Day, the second-biggest beef-eating day after 
Independence Day.That's equivalent in weight to 2,000 school buses. . . . Los 
Angeles is the fourth-leading destination for domestic business travel this 
year, according to management consultants Runzheimer International. The city 
tied with New York for second place in 1992, the last time the survey was 
conducted. The leading destination in both years was Chicago, according to 345 
travel managers surveyed. 
</P>
