<HEADLINE>
<P>
ABT SETS CASTING FOR COSTA MESA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ZAN DUBIN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cynthia Harvey will dance the title role in American Ballet Theatre's 
production of "Manon" on Sept. 20, opening night of the troupe's six-day 
engagement at the Orange County Performing Arts Center in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 Guillaume Graffin will appear opposite Harvey, and Gil Boggs and Kathleen 
Moore will handle supporting roles in Kenneth MacMillan's ballet, to be 
presented six times.It will be the first time ABT has performed the full-length 
"Manon" in Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
 In subsequent performances of "Manon," the leading roles will go to Julie Kent 
and Robert Hill, Susan Jaffe and Charles Askegard. Each pair will dance "Manon" 
twice. 
</P>
<P>
 ABT will also give the first West Coast performances of James Kudelka's "Cruel 
World" on two mixed repertory programs that include Natalia Makarova's staging 
of "The Kingdom of the Shades" from "La Bayadere" and Twyla Tharp's "In the 
Upper Room." 
</P>
<P>
 Casting, subject to change, is as follows:  
</P>
<P>
 * Sept. 20, 8 p.m.: "Manon," Cynthia Harvey, Guillaume Graffin, Gil Boggs, 
Kathleen Moore. 
</P>
<P>
 * Sept. 21, 8 p.m.: "La Bayadere," Susan Jaffe, Parrish Maynard. "Cruel World" 
and "In the Upper Room," ensemble. 
</P>
<P>
 * Sept. 22, 8 p.m.: "La Bayadere," Harvey, Graffin. 
</P>
<P>
 * Sept. 23, 8 p.m.: "Manon," Julie Kent, Robert Hill, Keith Roberts, Christina 
Fagundes. 
</P>
<P>
 * Sept. 24, 2 p.m.: "Manon," Jaffe, Charles Askegard, Ethan Brown, Kathleen 
Moore. 
</P>
<P>
 * Sept. 24, 8 p.m.: "Manon," Harvey, Graffin, Boggs, Moore. 
</P>
<P>
 * Sept. 25, 2 p.m.: "Manon," Kent, Hill, Roberts, Fagundes. 
</P>
<P>
 * Sept. 25, 8 p.m.: "Manon," Jaffe, Askegard, Brown, Christine Dunham. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets, $18-$55, are available through Ticketmaster, (213) 480-3232, or (714) 
740-2000 or at the center box office, 600 Town Center Drive, Costa Mesa, (714) 
556-2787. 
</P>
