<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Children's Museum at La Habra has been awarded a $112,500 operating grant 
from the Institute of Museum Services, a federal agency that supports a variety 
of institutions, from art museums to zoos, that work to educate the public. The 
museum has received nine IMS grants in 14 years; this year's is for the maximum 
agency grant amount. It totals about 15% of the museum's $500,000 operating 
budget. 
</P>
<P>
 Compiled by Kathy Stickel 
</P>
