<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
FIREFIGHTERS NAMED IN ARSON CASE TO FILE CLAIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An attorney for two firefighters named as arson suspects in the devastating 
Calabasas-Malibu fire last fall said this week that he will bring legal action 
against Los Angeles County for damage to their reputations. 
</P>
<P>
 Larry Feldman, who represented the boy who won a multimillion-dollar 
out-of-court settlement in a molestation claim against superstar Michael 
Jackson, said he expects to file a claim against the county within two weeks, a 
required first step before a lawsuit.A suit can be filed if the county fails to 
respond to the claim. 
</P>
<P>
 Steven Shelp, a Los Angeles County firefighter, and Nicholas Durepo, a 
volunteer firefighter in Manhattan Beach, were identified by sheriff's 
officials as suspected arsonists in one of the worst fires in Los Angeles 
history. 
</P>
<P>
 Neither man was charged with a crime, and the Los Angeles County district 
attorney's office recently announced that officials had insufficient evidence 
to prosecute and were no longer investigating them. The announcement did not 
exonerate the men, who have denied that they set the fire. 
</P>
<P>
 A sheriff's spokesman said the department has received no formal notice of the 
action and had no comment. 
</P>
