<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: VALENCIA; CALARTS TO 
GET $25 MILLION FOR EARTHQUAKE REPAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 California Institute of the Arts, the Valencia college heavily damaged during 
the Northridge earthquake, has been awarded almost $25 million in federal funds 
for repairs, officials with the Federal Emergency Management Agency said. 
</P>
<P>
 FEMA spokesman Russ Edmonston said the private arts college has been 
authorized to receive more than $24.9 million to rebuild earthquake-damaged 
structures.The majority of the funds -- about $23 million -- will repair 
structural damage to CalArts' 500,000-square-foot main building. 
</P>
<P>
 As quake repairs began, courses were held in a variety of impromptu locations. 
Temple Beth Shalom in Newhall, a vacant Lockheed research center in Valencia, 
the Magic Moments Theatre at Six Flags Magic Mountain amusement park, the Santa 
Clarita YMCA, a health club at the Vista Village shopping center and Le Studio 
in Pasadena all served as CalArts classrooms in the weeks after the temblor. 
