<P>
 In responding to a preseason questionnaire, Donnelly listed winning five games 
as the Seahawks' team goal. While that might seem unambitious to some, five 
victories in a season at Ocean View is like snow in the Southland--it don't 
happen often. If the Seahawks attain their goal, it would give them five more 
victories than they've had the last three seasons combined. Ocean View, which 
finished last in the Sunset League last season, has lost 29 consecutive games. 
Entering a new league might be just the thing to spark a turnaround; Donnelly 
sure hopes so. "I think we're a lot better than last year," Donnelly said. "I 
think we're going to get a few (victories)." If so, Silva must come through 
with a standout season. Silva, a member of the varsity for three seasons and a 
two-year starter, is a powerful runner who is also capable of big plays. 
Helping Silva break free is Traxler's job. SCHEDULE 
</P>
