<HEADLINE>
<P>
BARGAINS / GERI COOK: HIDES TO GO SEEK; NOT ONLY ARE PRICE TAGS DRASTICALLY CUT 
AT WILSON'S SOLE OUTLET STORE, BUT A SMALL RIP CAN MEAN A HUGE BARGAIN ON 
LEATHER. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GERI COOK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When a new season is around the corner, what a pleasant feeling it is to have 
some dazzling out fit, new and just waiting for the first cool and appropriate 
occasion. 
</P>
<P>
 When I stopped to research the new location of Wilson's Outlet store, my son 
spotted a silky suede bomber jacket in an elegant shade of coral. The price tag 
read $49.95, and he crowed, "Hey, I saw this somewhere for $200!" He hasn't 
been into this bargain shopping very much, but became a believer instantly. Now 
that splendid suede is waiting in his closet for the first nippy day of fall. 
</P>
<P>
 This new Wilson's store in Burbank is located in what was a Security Pacific 
bank and just around the corner from its previous location. A sign in the 
window screams, "Nothing over $99.99," which foretells of the bargains, if 
you've priced leather apparel lately. 
</P>
<P>
 As you enter, on the left you'll see the women's department and will learn 
just how drastic the price cuts are. Some brightly colored and very supple 
leather halter tops that were $69.95 are tagged at $19.95 with skirts to match 
for $29.99 (originally $119.99). So an outfit that was close to $200 can be 
purchased for $50. Suede shorts in a multitude of colors are $9.99, one-third 
of the original price. 
</P>
<P>
 Most of the inventory at this sole outlet store is made up of close-outs from 
the 500-plus stores of the Wilson's chain across the country. It might be 
merchandise from last season or overruns from the current season, or perhaps 
some broken sizes from the current line. 
</P>
<P>
 There are, however, some racks for damaged goods on the right and in the 
middle of the men's department, and it's these that the seasoned shoppers, 
looking for a treasure, check out on a regular basis. They might find a $400 
leather coat for $50 because of a small rip -- it has happened. Some men's 
leather pants that originally were selling for $149 were slashed to $29.99 
because of a scratch, and a man's handsome black leather car coat that was $325 
is now $99.99, due to a one-inch rip that could easily be covered with a 
colorful patch of some sort. 
</P>
<P>
 In the bins toward the center of the store are accessories -- a few scattered 
handbags, gloves and attache cases -- all drastically reduced and always worth 
checking. I still wish I had picked up the $245 attache case for $39.99, and by 
not doing so broke one of the cardinal rules for bargain shoppers. Don't 
procrastinate -- pounce! 
</P>
<P>
 Sizes for both men and women run from extra small to extra large. WHERE TO 
SHOP 
</P>
<P>
 What: Wilson's Outlet store. 
</P>
<P>
 Location: 3117 W. Magnolia Blvd., Burbank. 
</P>
<P>
 Hours: 10 a.m. to 7 p.m. Monday to Saturday, 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Cards: American Express, Discover, MasterCard, Visa. 
</P>
<P>
 Call: (818) 841-7789. 
</P>
</TEXT>
