<P>
 This former Sea View League member receives a boost from two former players. 
The Roadrunners' attack revolves around Caldwell, who returns to the team after 
living in Texas in 1993. As a starter on the varsity in 1992, Caldwell gained 
507 yards in 94 carries (a 5.4-yard average) and scored two touchdowns. "He's 
the only speed we have on the football field," Witte said. "We need 1,000 yards 
from him and we think we can get it." Killingbeck returns after taking a year 
off to concentrate on baseball and basketball. He started at cornerback toward 
the end of his sophomore season, but will play offense exclusively. Witte is 
relying on Killingbeck to operate the Roadrunners' option attack. "We're very 
pleased to have them back," Witte said. "We need them." SCHEDULE 
