<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FOOTBALL '94 / GOLDEN WEST LEAGUE; OCEAN VIEW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 1993 RECORDS 
</P>
<P>
 OVERALL: 0-10 
</P>
<P>
 LEAGUE: 0-7 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 COACH: John Donnelly 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 0-10 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 RETURNING STARTERS 
</P>
<P>
 OFF: 3 
</P>
<P>
 DEF: 2 04,27,05,05,05 TOP RETURNERS OFF DEF YR Jared Delacuica, 5-7, 135 WR DB 
Jr. Chris De Groodt, 6-0, 215 OL DL Jr. Geoff Hansen, 5-10, 185 QB DL Sr. Juan 
Lucero, 6-2, 245 OL DL Jr. Brett McMahon, 5-9, 200 OL LB Sr. Ted Norman, 5-11, 
180 RB DB Jr. Calvin Silva, 6-2, 220 RB LB Sr. Nathan Traxler, 6-2, 250 OL DL 
Sr. * 04,25,05,05,05 TOP NEWCOMERS OFF DEF YR Jason Hoffman, 5-8, 145 RB DB Sr. 
Mike Ketchum, 5-10, 190 OL LB So. Ray Marshall, 6-2, 195 TE LB So. Joey Seanoa, 
5-11, 230 OL DL So. OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 In responding to a preseason questionnaire, Donnelly listed winning five games 
as the Seahawks' team goal. While that might seem unambitious to some, five 
victories in a season at Ocean View is like snow in the Southland--it don't 
happen often. If the Seahawks attain their goal, it would give them five more 
victories than they've had the last three seasons combined. Ocean View, which 
finished last in the Sunset League last season, has lost 29 consecutive games. 
Entering a new league might be just the thing to spark a turnaround; Donnelly 
sure hopes so. "I think we're a lot better than last year," Donnelly said. "I 
think we're going to get a few (victories)." If so, Silva must come through 
with a standout season. Silva, a member of the varsity for three seasons and a 
two-year starter, is a powerful runner who is also capable of big plays. 
Helping Silva break free is Traxler's job. SCHEDULE 
</P>
<P>
 September 9 vs. Costa Mesa at Westminster HS; 16 at Newport Harbor; 23 vs. 
Century at Huntington Beach HS; 29 vs. Estancia at Newport Harbor HS. 
</P>
<P>
 October 7 vs. Marina at Westminster HS; 14 vs. Saddleback at Santa Ana 
Stadium; 20 vs. Servite at Huntington Beach HS; 28 vs. Santa Ana at Huntington 
Beach HS. 
</P>
<P>
 November 3 vs. Tustin at Westminster HS; 10 at Westminster. 
</P>
